In Karachi (1962–1966), 

M. balsamina

, available almost throughout the year, was infested by both 

B. cucurbitae

(listed as 

Dacus cucurbitae

) and 

Dacus ciliatus

, with total infestation rates of 4% in January up to 100% in February, 35% in March, 6% in April, 20% in August, 5% in September, almost 100% in November and subsiding to 3% in December. 
